-- Slovenia Beats 10-Man Algeria 1-0 to Lead in Group Including U.S., U.K.
-- Peter-Joseph Hegarty
-- 2010-06-13T13:23:34Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-13/slovenia-beats-10-man-algeria-1-0-goes-top-of-world-cup-group-c.html

          
          
             Slovenia beat 10-man Algeria 1-0 in
Polokwane, South Africa, to go top of World Cup Group C. Robert
Koren got the goal in the 79th minute.  
 Earlier, Abdelkader Ghezzal of Algeria was dismissed for a
second yellow card.  
 England drew 1-1 with the U.S. in the same group yesterday.  
 Later today Serbia plays Ghana and Germany meets Australia,
both in Group D.  
          
          


  


        